➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
I recently listened to an awesome PODCast from an overseas contractor - talking about real world training and practicality vs. what I call the IG "Gucci Insta famous training companies". 1️⃣-Be realistic on your skill sets and fundamentals. 
Why-  if you are a civilian with no military experience would you take training for CQC- Close Quarters Combat
2️⃣- Vet- Vet the instructors can't say it enough !
Watch out for the chest thumpers who shout their war stories 🗣and alleged SF-CIA-SEAL-GRS-BW certifications . True quiet professionals don't have to advertise . 
3️⃣-Proliferation of tactical training companies on Instagram and Facebook. 
How do you choose ? There's the whole slick IG famous instructors with their skinny jeans  wearing - Go Pro using - bible thumping God given tactical knowledge and experience or you can take a look at the "real world combat hardened and also Civilian Quiet Professionals" who teach "practicality and realistic-honest to God training based on "real world concepts ". 4️⃣-Firearms and tactical training is for one Purpose and 1 purpose only ! To STOP the Threat against you and your's. 
Could you handle the totality of taking a LIFE?? My 2 cents.
